<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Saving a token:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Manage access token</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>On the right, paste the copied token from the clipboard. To the right, enter <strong>plentymarkets</strong>, for example.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>OK</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1200">9.2. “plentyBase not connected. Check status”</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The error message “plentyBase not conneected. Check status` refers to different connection problems that may occur with plentyBase. First, make sure that you have correctly generated <strong>and</strong> saved the plenty access token <a href="#700">as described above</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you are using a Fritz!Box, connection problems might be directly related to it. Users operating a Fritz!Box can find a suitable forum <a href="https://forum.plentymarkets.com/t/es-kann-keine-verbindung-zu-plentybase-hergestellt-werden-fritzbox-benutzer-loesungsvorschlag/607564" target="_blank" rel="noopener">in this forum topic</a>.</p>
</div>
